               <head>Divan-i Nishat</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Dīvān-i Nishāṭ by ‘Abd al-Vahhāb Nishāṭ Iṣfahānī, - 1828 or 1829</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100084" n="1" xml:id="Uk_Or_15958-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22084">Dīvān-i Nishāṭ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_22084">دیوان نشاط </title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Collected poetical works of ‘Abd al-Vahhāb Iṣfahānī, called <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_1424616" ref="Persian_0147" role="aut">Nishāṭ</persName> (d. 1244/1828-9). This is the earliest recorded manuscript, and is also probably the first known from the hand of the renowned calligrapher Muḥammad Mahdī Farāhānī called <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7665" role="art">‘Ishrat</persName>.
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <filiation />
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_1424616">‘Abd al-Vahhāb Nishāṭ Iṣfahānī, - 1828 or 1829</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" type="supplied" key="person_1424616">عبد الوهّاب نشاط اصفهانی</persName>
                     </author>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
